<div class='modal fade' tabindex='-1'>
  <div class='modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered modal-dialog-scrollable modal-lg'>
    <form class='modal-content' action='' data-sk-channel='settings-edit'>
      <div class='modal-header'>
        <div class='modal-title'>
          <span class='mdi mdi-cogs mdi-18px'></span>
          <span class='ml-1'>Settings</span>
        </div>
        <button type='button' class='btn-close' data-bs-dismiss='modal'>
          <span class='mdi mdi-close'></span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class='modal-body'>
        <ul class="nav nav-tabs nav-justified mb-3">
          <li class="nav-item">
            <button class="nav-link active" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#general" type="button">General</button>
          </li>
          <li class="nav-item">
            <button class="nav-link" data-bs-toggle="tab" data-bs-target="#smartSteamLoader" type="button">SmartSteamLoader</button>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class="tab-content">
          <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="general">
            <div class='card'>
              <div class='card-title border-b border-solid border-primary'>
                <span class='mdi mdi-cloud mdi-18px'></span>
                <span class='ml-1'>SteamCloud</span>
              </div>
              <div class='card-body !p-2'>
                <p class='text-xs mb-2 text-center'>
                  To add support for game save backups, SteamLauncher uses an external tool which is
                  <a href='https://github.com/mtkennerly/ludusavi' target='_blank' class='link'>ludusavi</a>
                  and by entering you can set custom paths and change settings.<br /><b class='text-red-500'>Warning: Do not
                    use backup and restore of saves directly from
                    <a href='https://github.com/mtkennerly/ludusavi' target='_blank' class='link'>ludusavi</a>,
                    SteamLauncher uses a different logic. When adding a custom path, set the name without special characters
                    ("HomefrontÂ®: The Revolution" to "Homefront: The Revolution").</b>
                </p>
                <button type='button' class='btn btn-block btn-neutral uppercase' data-sk='open-ludusavi'>open ludusavi</button>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class='card'>
              <div class='card-title'>
                <span class='mdi mdi-lock-check mdi-18px'></span>
                <span class='ml-1'>SSL Certificate Verification</span>
              </div>
              <div class='card-body'>
                <select class='form-select !rounded-none' name='httpsRejectUnauthorized' required>
                  <option value='true' {{#if data.httpsRejectUnauthorized}}selected{{/if}}>Enabled</option>
                  <option value='false' {{#unless data.httpsRejectUnauthorized}}selected{{/unless}}>Disabled</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class='form-text text-center p-2'>If you encounter the "unable to verify the first certificate" error,
                try disabling the ssl certificate verification. If this value is changed, restart the app.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="tab-pane fade" id="smartSteamLoader">
            <div class='card'>
              <div class='card-title'>
                <span class='mdi mdi-lock-check mdi-18px'></span>
                <span class='ml-1'>SSE Persist</span>
              </div>
              <div class='card-body'>
                <select class='form-select !rounded-none' name='ssePersist' required>
                  <option value='true' {{#if data.ssePersist}}selected{{/if}}>Enabled</option>
                  <option value='false' {{#unless data.ssePersist}}selected{{/unless}}>Disabled</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class='form-text text-center p-2'>Don't exit the loader. Required for games that uses batch file (.bat) or which launch multiple executables.</div>
            </div>
            <div class='card'>
              <div class='card-title'>
                <span class='mdi mdi-lock-check mdi-18px'></span>
                <span class='ml-1'>SSE Inject Dll</span>
              </div>
              <div class='card-body'>
                <select class='form-select !rounded-none' name='sseInjectDll' required>
                  <option value='true' {{#if data.sseInjectDll}}selected{{/if}}>Enabled</option>
                  <option value='false' {{#unless data.sseInjectDll}}selected{{/unless}}>Disabled</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class='form-text text-center p-2'>Inject steamclient(64).dll module into process instead of waiting for game to load it itself. If the game uses steam.dll you might need this to be turned on.</div>
            </div>
            <div class='card'>
              <div class='card-title'>
                <span class='mdi mdi-lock-check mdi-18px'></span>
                <span class='ml-1'>SSE Paranoid Mode</span>
              </div>
              <div class='card-body'>
                <select class='form-select !rounded-none' name='sseParanoidMode' required>
                  <option value='true' {{#if data.sseParanoidMode}}selected{{/if}}>Enabled</option>
                  <option value='false' {{#unless data.sseParanoidMode}}selected{{/unless}}>Disabled</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class='form-text text-center p-2'>Warn you first if the steam client process is running before launching the game.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class='modal-footer'>
        <button type='submit' class='btn btn-block btn-green'>Save</button>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
